From 979ff827c11e6954db952a79f638fdba43172cef Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mainframe98 <k.s.werf@hotmail.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Oct 2025 19:07:42 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 04/50] PHP-Parser: Name resolve all nodes before traversing

Summary:
Previously, the name resolving was interleaved with the other visitors.
Most of the time this is fine, but in certain cases we seek deep into
the ast, where not all names have been resolved yet, such as trait use
statements. This results in relative names dependent on a use statement,
rather than the fully qualified name that had been expected.

This isn't an issue yet because this code base isn't using namespaces
yet, but will be once it does.

This doesn't seem to slow down the script much if at all.
A full rebuild of the phorge code base is about as quick as before.

Test Plan:
I did not test this directly, but I presume the following:
* Create a phutil library with namespaces and traits
* Use traits with relative names through use statements
* Observe differences in output

Reviewers: O1 Blessed Committers, avivey

Reviewed By: O1 Blessed Committers, avivey

Subscribers: tobiaswiese, valerio.bozzolan, Matthew, Cigaryno

Maniphest Tasks: T16289

Differential Revision: https://we.phorge.it/D26456
---
 support/lib/extract-symbols-with-php-parser.php | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/support/lib/extract-symbols-with-php-parser.php b/support/lib/extract-symbols-with-php-parser.php
index 7e5af1c7df84..1d87248f0f0b 100755
--- a/support/lib/extract-symbols-with-php-parser.php
+++ b/support/lib/extract-symbols-with-php-parser.php
@@ -158,6 +158,9 @@ function phutil_parse_file(
 
   $traverser = new PhpParser\NodeTraverser();
   $traverser->addVisitor(new PhpParser\NodeVisitor\NameResolver());
+  $ast = $traverser->traverse($ast);
+
+  $traverser = new PhpParser\NodeTraverser();
   $traverser->addVisitor($doc_block_visitor);
   $traverser->addVisitor($call_visitor);
   $traverser->addVisitor($declaration_visitor);
